# GitHub push workflow

After completing implementation work in this repo (fixes, features, refactors):

1. **Build** the project (`dotnet build -c Release` in `CS2 Combined/CS2 Combined/`).
2. **Commit** all relevant changes with a concise message focused on why.
3. **Push** to GitHub: `git push -u origin HEAD` on `main`.

Remote: `https://github.com/MoneyMan82/CS-2-External.git`

Do this at the end of every task that changes code — do not wait for the user to ask.

Skip commit/push only when:
- The user explicitly says not to commit or push
- There are no file changes to commit
- The work was question-only or review-only with no edits

Never force-push to `main`. Never update git config.
